text: Jannik Kohlbacher (born 19 July 1995) is a German handball player. He plays for Rhein-Neckar Löwen and the German national team. He took part in the 2016 European Men's Handball Championship. He was born in Bensheim. In March 2020, during the 2019–20 coronavirus pandemic, Kohlbacher tested positive for COVID-19. ==References== Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Handball players Category:Sportspeople from Hesse
